# Implementation Plan: AI Self-Healing Build Engine v2

## The Vision (Marketing Pitch)

> **"MicrOps doesn't just deploy your code. It fixes it."**
>
> Every other platform (Vercel, Railway, Render) shows you a red error and says "fix it yourself." MicrOps is the only deployment platform with a **Principal DevOps AI Agent** that reads the failure logs, diagnoses the root cause, patches your build config, and **autonomously retries the deployment** — all before you even read the error message.

---

## Current State (What You Have)

| Layer | Status | Gaps |
|-------|--------|------|
| **Preflight Scanner** | ✅ Scans repo file tree, detects runtime/framework | Only checks file presence. Doesn't read `tsconfig.json`, doesn't validate `vite.config`, doesn't check for TypeScript strict errors. |
| **Diagnostic Engine (Tier-1)** | ✅ 6 regex rules for common failures | Rules are reactive (post-failure). No detection for TS errors, ESLint, missing env vars in code, or monorepo structures. |
| **Diagnostic Engine (Tier-2)** | ✅ OpenAI GPT-4o-mini fallback | Good, but it only suggests a fix — it doesn't **apply** it automatically. The user must click "Apply Fix" manually. |
| **Apply Fix** | ✅ 1-click button in Dashboard | Only patches `installCommand`, `buildCommand`, or `runtime`. Cannot patch Dockerfile, cannot add missing dependencies, cannot fix TypeScript config. |

